- switch statement: Evaluates an expression and executes the corresponding case block.
/ Declara칞칚o switch: Avalia uma express칚o e executa o bloco de c칩digo correspondente ao case.

- case label: Defines a specific value to match in the switch statement.
/ R칩tulo case: Define um valor espec칤fico para comparar na declara칞칚o switch.

- break statement: Exits the switch statement after a case block is executed.
/ Declara칞칚o break: Encerra a execu칞칚o da declara칞칚o switch ap칩s um bloco case ser executado.

- default case: Specifies a block of code to execute if no case matches.
/ Caso default: Especifica um bloco de c칩digo a ser executado se nenhum case corresponder.

- fall-through behavior: Omitting break allows execution to "fall through" to the next case.
/ Comportamento de queda: Omiss칚o do break permite que a execu칞칚o "caia" para o pr칩ximo case.

Example code | Exemplo de c칩digo:

public class SwitchCaseExample {
    public static void main(String[] args) {
        int dayOfWeek = 3; // Example: 3 represents Tuesday
        String dayName;

        switch(dayOfWeek) {
            case 1: dayName = "Sunday"; break;
            case 2: dayName = "Monday"; break;
            case 3: dayName = "Tuesday"; break;
            case 4: dayName = "Wednesday"; break;
            case 5: dayName = "Thursday"; break;
            case 6: dayName = "Friday"; break;
            case 7: dayName = "Saturday"; break;
            default: dayName = "Invalid day"; break;
        }

        System.out.println("The day of the week is: " + dayName);
    }
}